The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) on Sunday April 19, confirmed eighty six new cases of Coronavirus bringing the total number to 627, and this got mixed reactions from Nigerians. After the news was shared on Twitter, singer Zlatan reacted to the post with laughing emojis. Presidential aide, Bashir Ahmad cautions singer Zlatan Bashir Ahmad, the Personal Assistant to President Buhari on New Media has now been forced to caution the singer for making light of the new Coronavirus cases. He wrote: ‘Zlatan, as President Buhari stated in his national broadcast on April 13th, ‘this is not a joke, it’s a matter of life and death.’ Source